üìù<br>

Content management system is a software (more often a set of softwares) that enables organizations to create, review, publish, and manage content in a central and collaborative environment. <br>

## ## Features

Content management system commonly consists the a set of tools.

- **Authoring**. 

- **Output generation**.  

- **Publishing**. 

- **Versioning**. 

## ## Benefits

Content management system has the following benefits. <br>

Separate content from format.

Easy collaboration. Content management system allows the collaboration among team members. It enables content writer and reviewers to work on the same project in parallel. 

Efficiency. 

Support version control. 

Scalbility. 
